X-SOURCE-ID:calendar_livewhale
SUMMARY:Alice Wong Memorial Event + Dim Sum Station
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260325T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260325T123000
DTSTAMP:20260224T150108Z
UID:20260325T180000Z-15401@calendar.santarosa.edu
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260325T110000
ATTACH:https://calendar.santarosa.edu/live/image/gid/3/width/80/height/80/
 crop/1/src_region/0,0,500,500/570_alice_wong_celebration_of_life_event_dis
 trict_calendar.rev.1772833670.png
CATEGORIES:Department Events,District Events
DESCRIPTION:Join the SRJC Disability Cultural Center (DCC) and APASS for a
  special Celebration of Life honoring Alice Wong\, a visionary Asian Ameri
 can disability rights activist whose work has shaped the Disability Visibi
 lity movement. The event will take place on March 25 from 11:00 AM–12:30
  PM in the SRJC Intercultural Center\, Pioneer Room 380\, and will include
  a livestream of the memorial happening in San Francisco with guest speake
 rs.  In addition to the livestream\, attendees are invited to gather in co
 mmunity with a dim sum station\, quote sharing\, and supplies to contribut
 e to a Disability Visibility quilt being created in her honor. All student
 s and community members are welcome to come reflect\, celebrate her legacy
 \, and take part in this collective!Intercultural Center - Pioneer Hall\, 
 Room 380\, Santa Rosa Campus  For more information\, visit: https://events
 .santarosa.edu/womxns-history-month-2026 (https://events.santarosa.edu/wom
 xns-history-month-2026)
LAST-MODIFIED:20260306T215023Z
LOCATION:Intercultural Center\, Santa Rosa Campus
URL:https://calendar.santarosa.edu/event/15401-alice-wong-memorial-event-d
 im-sum-station
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Join the SRJC Disability Cultural Center
  (DCC) and APASS for a special Celebration of Life honoring Alice Wong\, a
  visionary Asian American disability rights activist whose work has shaped
  the Disability Visibility movement. The event will take place on March 25
  from 11:00 AM–12:30 PM in the SRJC Intercultural Center\, Pioneer Room 
 380\, and will include a livestream of the memorial happening in San Franc
 isco with guest speakers.</p><p>  In addition to the livestream\, attendee
 s are invited to gather in community with a dim sum station\, quote sharin
 g\, and supplies to contribute to a Disability Visibility quilt being crea
 ted in her honor. All students and community members are welcome to come r
 eflect\, celebrate her legacy\, and take part in this collective!</p><p><s
 trong>Intercultural Center</strong> - <strong>Pioneer Hall\, Room 380</str
 ong>\, Santa Rosa Campus</p><p>  For more information\, visit: <a href="ht
 tps://events.santarosa.edu/womxns-history-month-2026" target="_blank" rel=
 "noopener">https://events.santarosa.edu/womxns-history-month-2026</a></p>
