X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Santa Rosa Junior College": "https://calendar.santarosa.edu/event/14535-meet-the-author-emilly-prado-funeral-for-flaca"}
X-SOURCE-ID:calendar_livewhale
SUMMARY:Meet the Author: Emilly Prado\, "Funeral For Flaca"
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260325T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260325T130000
DTSTAMP:20260205T163502Z
UID:20260325T190000Z-14535@calendar.santarosa.edu
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260325T120000
ATTACH:https://calendar.santarosa.edu/live/image/gid/3/width/80/height/80/
 crop/1/src_region/0,0,497,497/229_WHM-Logo-2024-JH_500x500.rev.1738968772.
 png
CATEGORIES:District Events
DESCRIPTION:Emilly Prado is an award-winning writer\, multidisciplinary ar
 tist\, and speaker whose work examines identity\, the systems that shape o
 ur lives\, and the power of storytelling across mediums. The author will s
 hare the evolving nature of finding her path as a writer\, drawing upon he
 r experiences as a first-generation Chicana and college student\, and self
 -proclaimed troublemaker who struggled with school and mental health. Atte
 ndees will hear a reading from Funeral for Flaca and view archival childho
 od photographs to better understand the author and how she found strength 
 through music and writing. Followed by a Q&amp\;A session.  For more infor
 mation\, visit: https://events.santarosa.edu/womxns-history-month-2026 (ht
 tps://events.santarosa.edu/womxns-history-month-2026)
LAST-MODIFIED:20260306T164944Z
LOCATION:Ellis Auditorium - Petaluma Campus
URL:https://calendar.santarosa.edu/event/14535-meet-the-author-emilly-prad
 o-funeral-for-flaca
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Emilly Prado is an award-winning writer\
 , multidisciplinary artist\, and speaker whose work examines identity\, th
 e systems that shape our lives\, and the power of storytelling across medi
 ums. The author will share the evolving nature of finding her path as a wr
 iter\, drawing upon her experiences as a first-generation Chicana and coll
 ege student\, and self-proclaimed troublemaker who struggled with school a
 nd mental health. Attendees will hear a reading from Funeral for Flaca and
  view archival childhood photographs to better understand the author and h
 ow she found strength through music and writing. Followed by a Q&amp\;A se
 ssion.</p><p>  For more information\, visit: <a href="https://events.santa
 rosa.edu/womxns-history-month-2026" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https:/
 /events.santarosa.edu/womxns-history-month-2026</a></p>
