X-SOURCE-ID:meetup_sonoma_county_go_wild_hikers
X-SOURCE:Meetup: Go Wild Hikers
X-SOURCE-URL:https://www.meetup.com/sonoma-county-go-wild-hikers/
UID:event_313771755@meetup.com
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTAMP:20260323T025119Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260328T113000
SUMMARY:Sonoma Valley Hike
DESCRIPTION:Go Wild Hikers\nThis is one of my favorite routes in this park
 . The trails we'll hike will pass through the park's northern boundary and
  offers views of Sonoma Valley and the Mayacamas Range. The property is an
  important piece of the Sonoma Valley Wildlife Corridor\, a collection of 
 protected lands allowing animals safe crossing on the valley floor. There'
 s a dog park right next to the regional park if your pup still has energy 
 to burn.\n\n**Where We Meet/Important Directions**\nSonoma Valley Regional
  Park\n13630 Highway 12\, Glen Ellen\, CA 95442\nGoing East on Hwy 12 towa
 rds Sonoma. **Pay Attention! The park is on the right a quick quarter of a
  mile past the Arnold Drive traffic light.**\nGive yourself plenty of time
  to arrive\, pay park fee and use the restroom. It often takes longer than
  you think.\n\n**The Hike (Group Hike #337)**\nWest Sutton Lake\, Woodland
  Star\, East Sutton Lake\, Valley of the Moon\, Black Canyon Creek and Cou
 gar trails - A loop hike\nLength - +/-4 miles/6.4 kilometers\nElevation ch
 ange - +/-500 feet/152 meters\nDifficulty - 5 out of 10 - mostly easy\nExp
 osures - 75 % sun/25% shade - rocky\, poison oak\, ticks and insects.\nBri
 ng plenty of water. At least 34 oz./1 liter.\nDogs - Yes\, well behaved do
 gs on a leash are welcome.\nFacilities at trail head - Dog Park\, Water\, 
 picnic tables and restrooms.\nCost - $5 cash.\nParking - $8 per vehicle or
  free with Regional Park pass.\nRemember to wear appropriate hiking shoes\
 , bring plenty of water for your dog too\, a hat\, snacks & layered clothi
 ng.\nPlease Do Not Use Any scented products the day of a group hike!\nOf c
 ourse\, we will all look out for each other but ultimately\, hikers are re
 sponsible for their own safety and well-being during hikes.\n\n**After Hik
 e Coffee/Food**\nLes Pascals (French bakery)\n13758 Arnold Dr\, Glen Ellen
 \, CA 95442\n[(707) 934-8378](https://www.google.com/search?q=french+baker
 y+glen+ellen&oq=french+bakery+Glen+ellen&gs_lcrp=EgZjaHJvbWUqDAgAECMYJxiAB
 BiKBTIMCAAQIxgnGIAEGIoFMhAIARAuGK8BGMcBGIAEGI4FMgYIAhBFGEAyCAgDEAAYFhgeMgg
 IBBAAGBYYHjIICAUQABgWGB4yCggGEAAYgAQYogTSAQg5OTUwajBqN6gCCLACAfEFED_C7AGwj
 rs&sourceid=chrome&ie=UTF-8#)\nhttps://www.lespascalspatisserie.com/\n\n**
 When We Meet**\nSaturday March 28\, 2026\n9:00 am - 11:30 am\nIf your plan
 s change after you sign up even if you're on the waitlist\, please update 
 your RSVP.\nDo Not Attend if you are sick\, running a fever\, were exposed
  to or have tested positive for Covid-19 or any other contagion!\nHike may
  be changed\, rescheduled or cancelled in case of excessive heat\, rain\, 
 smoke/AQI\, illness\, zombie apocalypse etc... Check your email the night 
 before for any possible changes.\n\n**Notice to New Hikers Only**\n**"When
  a New Hiker (never hiked with me before) doesn't show up (No Show) to the
 ir first hike with the group\, they will be removed (not banned) from the 
 group immediately."**
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/sonoma-county-go-wild-hikers/events/3
 13771755/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260313T221451Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260313T221451Z
CLASS:PUBLIC
END:VEVENT
