SUMMARY: *SPECIAL EVENT* Sunday Sessions with The Declan Wheel
DESCRIPTION:One time only\, see this special production of Elvis Costello
 's Return of the Spectacular Spinning Songbook!\n\nJoin us for the debut 
 of The Declan Wheel in this very special\, interactive Sunday Session Sho
 wcase! This locally produced rendition of Elvis Costello's Return of the 
 SPectacular Spinning Songbook features a spinning wheel where audience me
 mbers can take a turn deciding the setlist! While you watch in wonderment
  at this once in a lifetime local show\, Cajun Po' Boys will have an extr
 a special menu available and the Griffo team will be serving up our ever 
 rotating cocktail menu featuring our house-made Bloody Marys! Get there e
 arly and check out the Mitchell Thomas Duo featuring Faith Waligora http:
 //...this is one show you don't want to miss! See you Sundays!\n\nWho's P
 laying: The Declan Wheel: An Homage to Return of the Spectacular Spinning
  Songbook by Elvis Costello & the Imposters\n\nWho's Opening: Mitchell Th
 omas Duo featuring Faith Waligora\n\nWho's Cooking: Cajun Po' Boys\n\nWhe
 n: Sunday\, March 29th - Doors @ 1pm\n\nWhere: Griffo Distillery - 1320 S
 cott Street\, Petaluma\, CA\n\nPlease RSVP for this FREE\, All Ages Event
 . Space is Limited.\n\nAbout the Band:\n\nThe Declan Wheel is an Homage t
 o Elvis Costello & the Imposters comprised of 7 local musicians who'll of
 fer the audience members to take a turn on the Spectacular Spinning Songb
 ook Wheel to pick the tunes the band will play featuring the talents of:\
 n\nFaith Waligora\, Vocals (Space Orchestra\, Crooked Shoes\, Mitchell Th
 omas Band)\n\nTim Sarter\, Bass (King Baby and the Mighty Bogarts\, Whisk
 ey Dent\, The Beguilers et al)\n\nTim Gahagan\, Drums (Whiskey Dent\, Spi
 ke Sikes’ Monktet\, Derek Irving combo et al)\n\nSteve Della Maggiora (Ki
 ng Baby and the Mighty Bogarts\, Smorgy Music et al)\n\nDan Curry\, Vocal
 s (King Baby and the Mighty Bogarts\, The Roadies)\n\nEric Balmy\, guitar
  (King Baby and the Mighty Bogarts\, et al)\n\nChris Ashley\, guitar (The
  Roadies et al)
