DESCRIPTION:The Music Department of Santa Rosa Junior College presents a j
 azz concert by the Bennett Friedman Quartet on Thursday\, April 2\, at 7:3
 0 PM in Newman Auditorium on the SRJC campus. Guitarist Randy Vincent\, ba
 ssist Jeff Denson\, and drummer Kendrick Freeman will be featured.  The qu
 artet will perform "Take Five" by Paul Desmond\, compositions of Bobby Hut
 cherson\, Wayne Shorter\, and others.  General admission is $15\, and $10 
 for students and seniors. Parking on campus is $4. Proceeds from the conce
 rt benefit the SRJC Foundation Jazz Studies Fund.Visit SRJC's Music Depart
 ment website here! (https://music.santarosa.edu/events)
LAST-MODIFIED:20260306T221435Z
LOCATION:Newman Auditorium (Emeritus Hall) - Santa Rosa Campus
URL:https://calendar.santarosa.edu/event/16291-bennett-friedman-quartet
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  The Music Department of Santa Rosa Junio
 r College presents a jazz concert by the Bennett Friedman Quartet on Thurs
 day\, April 2\, at 7:30 PM in Newman Auditorium on the SRJC campus. Guitar
 ist Randy Vincent\, bassist Jeff Denson\, and drummer Kendrick Freeman wil
 l be featured.<br /><br />  The quartet will perform "Take Five" by Paul D
 esmond\, compositions of Bobby Hutcherson\, Wayne Shorter\, and others.<br
  /><br />  General admission is $15\, and $10 for students and seniors. Pa
 rking on campus is $4. Proceeds from the concert benefit the SRJC Foundati
 on Jazz Studies Fund.</p><p><a href="https://music.santarosa.edu/events" t
 arget="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit SRJC's Music Department website here!<
 /a></p>
