SUMMARY:Luis & N Burma at Annadel
DESCRIPTION:Go Wild Hikers\nA beautiful hike to take in the wildflowers of
  spring. We'll start by going up Richardson to Lake Ilsanjo\, take a break
  at the lake or the gazebo\, then proceed to Luis and down N Burma to Chan
 nel trail. Best for individuals with at least a moderate level of fitness.
 \n\n**Where We Meet/Important Directions**\nTrione - Annadel State Park\n*
 *Do Not Use Your GPS! Follow These Direction.**\nMontgomery Drive to Chann
 el Drive to the Very (Dead) End! **Way past the pay kiosk!** There is a La
 rge Parking Lot and the Warren Richardson Trail head. Much Farther than yo
 u think....Keep going until you see us. Give yourself enough time to arriv
 e\, pay park fee and use the bathroom. It often takes longer than you thin
 k.\n\n**The Hike (Group Hike #338)**\nRichardson\, Luis\, N Burma and Chan
 nel Trails - A loop hike\nDistance - 6 miles/9.7 kilometers\nElevation cha
 nge - 830 feet/253 meters\nDifficulty - 6+ out of 10 - Moderately easy\nEx
 posures - 30 % sun/70% shade - rocky\, maybe muddy\, poison oak\, ticks/in
 sects.\nMust be sure footed (confident and competent)!\nBring plenty of wa
 ter. At least 68 oz./2 liter.\nDogs - Are not allowed\nFacilities at trail
  head - Shade\, picnic tables and toilet.\nCost - $5 Cash.\nParking - $7 S
 tate Parks fee Or Free with your State Park Pass.\nRemember to wear approp
 riate hiking shoes\, bring plenty of water\, a hat\, a snack and layered c
 lothing.\nPlease Do Not Use Any scented products the day of a group hike!\
 nOf course\, we will all look out for each other but ultimately\, hikers a
 re responsible for their own safety and well-being during hikes.\n\n**Afte
 r Hike Gathering?**\n**Pascaline**\n1021 Hahman Drive\nSanta Rosa\, CA 954
 05\n707.303.7151\nOpen Daily: 8:00 am – 4:00 pm\nLunch Daily: 10:30 am 
 – 2:30 pm\n\n**When We Meet**\nSunday April 5\, 2026\n830 am - 1130 am\n
 If your plans change after you sign up even if you're on the waitlist\, pl
 ease update your RSVP.\nDo Not Attend if you are sick\, running a fever\, 
 were exposed to or have tested positive for Covid-19 or any other contagio
 n!\nHike may be changed\, postponed or cancelled due to excessive heat\, s
 moke/AQI\, rain\, illness or zombie apocalypses etc.. Check your email the
  night before for any possible changes.\n\n**Notice to New Hikers Only**\n
 **"When a New Hiker (never hiked with me before) doesn't show up (No Show)
  to their first hike with the group\, they will be removed (not banned) fr
 om the group immediately."**
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.meetup.com/sonoma-county-go-wild-hikers/events/3
 13859015/
