BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Santa Rosa Junior College": "https://calendar.santarosa.edu/event/16277-monet-venice-visiting-artist-lecture-with-professor-he"}
X-SOURCE-ID:calendar_livewhale
SUMMARY:"Monet & Venice" Visiting Artist Lecture with Professor Heidi Sale
 h
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260414T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260414T130000
DTSTAMP:20260306T121408Z
UID:20260414T190000Z-16277@calendar.santarosa.edu
RECURRENCE-ID;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260414T120000
ATTACH:https://calendar.santarosa.edu/live/image/gid/1/width/80/height/80/
 crop/1/src_region/0,0,337,337/567_calendar_square_-_claude_monet_painting.
 rev.1772827972.png
CATEGORIES:Arts,Department Events,District Events
DESCRIPTION:Please join Art History Professor Heidi Saleh for an upcoming 
 lecture examining Claude Monet's celebrated 1908 Venetian campaign.  Desig
 ned as a companion to the Monet and Venice exhibition currently on view (3
 /21/26 – 7/26/26) at the de Young Museum in San Francisco\, this talk wi
 ll explore the historical and stylistic context of Monet's time in the Flo
 ating City. We will analyze his approach to seriality\, his technique for 
 capturing light on water\, and how these canvases fit into the broader tra
 jectory of late Impressionism.  Whether you have already visited the de Yo
 ung exhibition or are planning a trip\, this lecture will provide a deeper
  framework for appreciating and engaging with these works.  For more infor
 mation\, visit SRJC's Agrella Art Gallery website! (https://art-gallery.sa
 ntarosa.edu/exhibition/visiting-artist-lecture-series-spring-2026)  Also o
 n Zoom:&#160\;https://santarosa-edu.zoom.us/j/85748104401 (https://santaro
 sa-edu.zoom.us/j/85748104401)&#160\;  Meeting ID: 857 4810 440
LAST-MODIFIED:20260306T202105Z
LOCATION:Doyle Library\, Room 146 - Santa Rosa Campus
URL:https://calendar.santarosa.edu/event/16277-monet-venice-visiting-artis
 t-lecture-with-professor-he
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Please join Art History Professor Heidi 
 Saleh for an upcoming lecture examining Claude Monet's celebrated 1908 Ven
 etian campaign.</p><p>  Designed as a companion to the Monet and Venice ex
 hibition currently on view (3/21/26 – 7/26/26) at the de Young Museum in
  San Francisco\, this talk will explore the historical and stylistic conte
 xt of Monet's time in the Floating City. We will analyze his approach to s
 eriality\, his technique for capturing light on water\, and how these canv
 ases fit into the broader trajectory of late Impressionism.</p><p>  Whethe
 r you have already visited the de Young exhibition or are planning a trip\
 , this lecture will provide a deeper framework for appreciating and engagi
 ng with these works.</p><p>  For more information\, visit <a href="https:/
 /art-gallery.santarosa.edu/exhibition/visiting-artist-lecture-series-sprin
 g-2026" target="_blank" rel="noopener">SRJC's Agrella Art Gallery website!
 </a></p><p>  Also on Zoom:&#160\;</p><p><a href="https://santarosa-edu.zoo
 m.us/j/85748104401" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://santarosa-edu.z
 oom.us/j/85748104401</a>&#160\;</p><p>  Meeting ID: 857 4810 440</p>
X-LIVEWHALE-ID:16277
X-LIVEWHALE-IMAGE:https://calendar.santarosa.edu/live/image/gid/1/width/80
 /height/80/crop/1/src_region/0\,0\,337\,337/567_calendar_square_-_claude_m
 onet_painting.rev.1772827972.png
X-LIVEWHALE-IMAGE-CAPTION:<em>The Church of San Giorgio Maggiore Venice\, 
