DESCRIPTION:Using the past\, to inform the present\, to shape the future. 
  From Dream Clubs in local colleges to a national movement\, undocumented 
 youth turned isolation into community and community into power. Whether yo
 u're into history\, social movements\, or you're simply curious about how 
 a disenfranchised community built national influence\, this conversation i
 s for you!Register here! (https://events.zoom.us/ev/Ari35dd7sJIXd1xyPWqFl8
 TB6Y-YQK7kmCwVt4RVvIF1H-qxG3hS~AnvT0N5dg7dUYGAFFZGL1RJZwCmuHCNaOQ_hA4u2EAc
 twtE3JnWx7OxGXg)  For more information\, visit the SRJC Undocu • Immigra
 nt • Dream Center Website (https://dream.santarosa.edu/workshops-events-
 2025-2026)
LAST-MODIFIED:20260227T211812Z
LOCATION:Zoom
URL:https://calendar.santarosa.edu/event/15545-lessons-from-the-dream-move
 ment
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Using the past\, to inform the present\,
  to shape the future.</p><p>  From Dream Clubs in local colleges to a nati
 onal movement\, undocumented youth turned isolation into community and com
 munity into power. Whether you're into history\, social movements\, or you
 're simply curious about how a disenfranchised community built national in
 fluence\, this conversation is for you!</p><p><a href="https://events.zoom
 .us/ev/Ari35dd7sJIXd1xyPWqFl8TB6Y-YQK7kmCwVt4RVvIF1H-qxG3hS~AnvT0N5dg7dUYG
